ng%2015%25%20in%20royalties%20from%20Yeezy%20sales%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F27%2Fbusiness%2Fkanye-west-adidas-yeezy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%20October%202023%20that%20the%20rapper%20is%20still%20entitled%20to%20royalties%20after%20Adidas%20cut%20ties%20with%20him%2C%20though%20it%20did%20not%20specify%20how%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rapper%20also%20accused%20Adidas%20of%20%26quot%3Brape%26quot%3B%20in%20an%20October%202022%20post%2C%20in%20which%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fstyle%2F2022%2F10%2Fadidas-ends-partnership-with-kanye-west%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eranted%20against%20the%20organization%20in%20all-caps%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20it%20announced%20the%20termination%20of%20its%20relationship%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20AM%20ADIDAS%20ADIDAS%20RAPED%20AND%20STOLE%20MY%20DESIGNS%2C%26quot%3B%20Ye's%20Instagram%20caption%20partially%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdidas%20has%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadidas-yeezy-kanye-west-ye-sneakers-loss-sell-shoes-antisemitism-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24300%20million%20of%20Yeezy%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%2C%20the%20company%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adidas-group.com%2Fen%2Fmedia%2Fnews-archive%2Fpress-releases%2F2024%2Fadidas-full-year-results-exceed-latest-expectations-company-deci%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearlier%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20bulk%20of%20the%20proceeds%20would%20go%20to%20charities%2C%20including%20the%20Anti-Defamation%20League%20and%20the%20Philonise%20%26amp%3B%20Keeta%20Floyd%20Institute%20for%20Social%20Change%2C%20Adidas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20press%20office%20for%20Adidas%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-accuses-adidas-fake-yeezy-suing-not-paying-royalties-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709007442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65dd5c596080194819fa5c16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-accuses-adidas-fake-yeezy-suing-not-paying-royalties-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ye%20also%20claimed%20that%20Adidas%20was%20suing%20him%20for%20%24250%20million%20and%20failed%20to%20pay%20him%20royalties%20or%20the%20sale%20of%20Yeezys%20after%20his%20fallout%20with%20the%20firm.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-accuses-adidas-fake-yeezy-suing-not-paying-royalties-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20the%202023%20Consumption%20Survey%20Is%20Not%20Comparable%20with%20Previous%20Rounds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F27093901%2F26172691320_ea02245a43_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20of%20India%20has%20finally%20conducted%20and%20released%20the%20Household%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey%20of%202022-23%20after%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20a%20Household%20Consumer%20Expenditure%20Survey%20(denoted%20as%20CES)%20was%20undertaken%20every%20five%20years.%20The%20last%20was%20in%202011-12.%20The%20current%20survey%E2%80%99s%20factsheet%2C%20published%20yesterday%2C%20is%20the%2010th%20CES.%20However%2C%20it%20should%20%3Cstrong%3Efirst%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20current%20CES%202022-23%20cannot%20be%20compared%20with%20the%20earlier%20CES%20rounds%20on%20account%20of%20a%20change%20in%20methodology.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecond%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20National%20Survey%20Organisation%20(NSO)%2C%20which%20conducts%20these%20always%2C%20has%20personally%20informed%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20that%20these%20are%20not%20comparable.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20HCES%202022-23%20reports%20also%20clearly%20point%20out%20%E2%80%9Cissues%20related%20to%20comparability%E2%80%9D%20and%20state%20that%20%E2%80%9CHCES%3A%202022-23%20has%20undergone%20some%20changes%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20surveys%20on%20consumption%20expenditures.%E2%80%9D%20and%20should%20not%20be%20compared%20with%20the%20earlier%20CES%20rounds.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStill%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20chief%20has%20claimed%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20poverty%20has%20declined%20to%20below%205%25%2C%20inferring%20that%20the%20HCES%202022%20is%20comparable%20to%20CES%202011-12%3B%20it%20is%20not.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThird%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20there%20is%20no%20current%20poverty%20line%20determined%20by%20NITI%20Aayog%20unlike%20the%20erstwhile%20Planning%20Commission.%20Thus%20it%20cannot%20be%20assumed%20that%20the%20HCES%202022-23%20indicates%20that%20the%20poverty%20is%20down%20to%20below%205%25.%20It%20is%20prudent%20to%20state%20that%20the%20whole%2027-page%20HCES%20factsheet%20remains%20silent%20on%20poverty%20estimation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20changes%20in%20methodology%20make%20HCES%20non-comparable%20to%20earlier%20CES.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20HCES%202022-23%2C%20sampling%20methodology%20has%20undergone%20significant%20change%20including%20stratum%2C%20and%20second-stage%20stratum.%20The%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erural%E2%80%99%20stratum%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efor%20HCES%202022-23%20consists%20of%20just%20two%20strata%2C%20the%20first%2C%20comprising%20of%20the%20villages%20within%20a%20distance%20of%205%20kilometres%20from%20the%20district%20headquarters%20and%20the%20rest%20are%20in%20the%20other%20strata.%20The%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eurban%E2%80%99%20strata%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%20classified%20based%20on%20%E2%80%98population%E2%80%99%20as%20well%20as%20%E2%80%98affluence%E2%80%99%20status.%20The%20s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eecond-stage%20stratum%20classification%20is%20now%20made%20on%20land%20for%20rural%20areas%20and%20car%20availability%20for%20urban%20areas%2C%20unlike%20the%20previous%20survey%20where%20the%20divisions%20were%20made%20based%20on%20household%20status%20and%20household%20activity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20rural%20areas%20and%20monthly%20per-capita%20income%20for%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erural%20second-stage%20stratum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20rural%20households%20were%20classified%20into%20three%20categories%20based%20on%20land%20availability%20based%20on%20state-level%20cut-off%20points%20as%20per%20the%20%E2%80%98Situation%20Assessment%20Survey%20of%20Agricultural%20Households%202019%E2%80%99.%20In%20a%20country%20where%20agricultural%20labourers%20outnumber%20cultivators%2C%20access%20to%20land%20remains%20limited%20let%20alone%20possession%20of%20land%20amongst%20the%20%E2%80%98highest%20order%E2%80%99%20as%20classified%20in%20the%20top%20two%20second-stage%20stratum.%20Land%20remains%20a%20leading%20factor%20in%20determining%20socio-economic%20well-being%2C%20and%20ought%20to%20be%20very%20well-off%20thereby%20having%20a%20higher%20consumption.%20For%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eurban%20areas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20households%20were%20classified%20based%20on%20the%20availability%20of%20four-wheeler%20cars%20for%20non-commercial%20use%2C%20with%20price%20of%20more%20than%20Rs%2010%20lakh%2C%20price%20less%20than%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20and%20other%20households%20without%20cars.%20In%20a%20country%20where%208%25%20of%20the%20households%20own%20a%20car%2C%20the%20urban%20top%20two%20second%20stage%20stratum%20will%20be%20among%20the%20wealthiest%20households%20having%20higher%20consumption.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESampling%20is%20done%20to%20ensure%20proper%20representation%20of%20households%20of%20different%20economic%20categories%3B%20however%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethere%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20higher%20representation%20of%20the%20well-off%20groups%20in%20the%20HCES%202022-23%20sampling%20approach%2C%20thereby%20resulting%20in%20higher%20consumption%20expenditure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHCES%202022-23%20factsheet%20lists%20out%20various%20methodological%20changes%20as%20well.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20there%20is%20change%20in%20item%20coverage%20with%20inclusion%20of%20new%20items%20and%20merging%20some%20of%20the%20obsolete%20items.%20Overall%2C%20the%20number%20of%20items%20covered%20has%20increased%20from%20347%20to%20405%20items.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecondly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20there%20have%20been%20changes%20in%20the%20questionnaire%20of%20the%20survey.%20Instead%20of%20a%20single%20questionnaire%20as%20used%20in%20earlier%20surveys%2C%20HCES%202022-23%20uses%20four%20separate%20questionnaires%20for%20food%2C%20consumables%20and%20services%20items%2C%20and%20durable%20goods%2C%20apart%20from%20a%20separate%20questionnaire%20for%20canvassing%20household%20characteristics%20to%20be%20used%20in%20three%20separate%20monthly%20visits%20in%20a%20quarter.%20Thus%2C%20there%20have%20been%20multiple%20visits%20for%20data%20collection%20instead%20of%20the%20usual%20practice%20of%20a%20single%20visit%20in%20the%20earlier%20surveys.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20results%20of%20the%20current%20HCES%20cannot%20be%20strictly%20comparable%20with%20the%202011-12%20CES%20or%20the%20earlier%20CES.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHCES%202022-23%20states%20that%20the%20average%20monthly%20per-capita%20consumption%20expenditure%20(MPCE)%20at%20current%20prices%20(without%20imputing%20value%20figures%20of%20the%20items%20received%20free%20by%20the%20households%20through%20various%20social%20welfare%20programmes)%20has%20increased%20to%20Rs%203%2C773%20for%20rural%20households%20(from%20Rs%201%2C430%20in%202011-12)%20and%20Rs%206%2C459%20for%20urban%20households%20(from%20Rs%202%2C630%20in%202011-12).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20numbers%20have%20been%20used%20in%20order%20to%20claim%20that%20poverty%20in%20India%20has%20been%20eradicated%20to%20just%205%25.%20However%2C%20the%20factsheet%20does%20not%20make%20any%20reference%20to%20poverty%20eradication.%20Nor%20is%20there%20any%20poverty%20line%20given%20by%20the%20HCES.%20So%20how%20is%20this%20value%20judgment%20made%20%E2%80%93%20that%20poverty%20has%20fallen%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20whole%2027-page%20factsheet%20is%20based%20on%20ratios%20and%20proportions.%20There%20are%20only%20a%20handful%20comparisons%20of%20actual%20numbers.%20These%C2%A0%20numbers%20too%20are%20not%20comparisons%20with%20real%20numbers.%20For%20the%20comparative%20perspective%2C%20a%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20(CPI)%20ought%20to%20be%20used%20to%20deflate%20the%20current%20expenditure%20to%20arrive%20at%20the%20real%20consumption%20expenditure.%20Without%20using%20CPI%2C%20any%20meaningful%20comparison%20should%20not%20be%20drawn.%20Just%20having%20a%20narrative%20with%20comparing%20numbers%20will%20add%20little%20value%20for%20want%20of%20data%20pertaining%20to%20quantity%20consumed%20and%20the%20expenditure%20incurred%20thereon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%20for%20the%20current%20HCES%202022-23%2C%20imputed%20cost%20for%20items%20received%20free%20of%20cost%20by%20the%20households%20through%20various%20social%20welfare%20programmes%20has%20been%20included%2C%20but%20the%20same%20is%20not%20undertaken%20for%20the%20earlier%20years%20in%20comparison.%20Thus%2C%20without%20parity%2C%20a%20comparison%20should%20not%20be%20drawn%20between%202011-12%20and%202022-23.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20consumption%20out%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(i)%20home-grown%2Fhome-produced%20stock%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(ii)%20gifts%2C%20loans%2C%20free%20collection%20and%20goods%20received%20in%20exchange%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20has%20been%20undertaken%20for%20the%20previous%20years%2C%20it%20has%20not%20been%20made%20explicit%20so%20to%20what%20is%20their%20proportion%20in%20the%20household%20consumption%20expenditure.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAny%20durable%20or%20non-durable%20taken%20on%20bank%20loans%2C%20equal%20monthly%20instalments%20or%20EMIs%2C%20or%20Kisan%20Credit%20Cards%20would%20eventually%20form%20part%20of%20consumption%20but%20will%20also%20add%20to%20the%20debt%20of%20the%20households.%20National%20Accounts%20Statistics%20are%20clearly%20stating%20that%20household%20consumption%20share%20is%20dropping%20since%202016%2C%20and%20household%20debt%20is%20increasing%3B%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20savings%20as%20a%20share%20of%20GDP%20have%20fallen%20under%20the%20current%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbove%20all%2C%20how%20is%20poverty%20supposed%20to%20have%20fallen%2C%20when%20both%20job%20growth%20has%20come%20down%20despite%20a%20larger%20number%20of%20school%20or%20university%20leavers%20enter%20the%20labour%20market.%20The%20real%20wages%20have%20stagnated%20between%202013%20and%202017%2C%20while%20the%20NSO%20Employment-Unemployment%20Round%20between%202004-5%20and%202011-12%20had%20shown%20an%20unmistakable%20and%20sustained%20rise%20in%20real%20wages.%20The%20graph%20below%20shows%20us%20trends%20in%20the%20real%20wages%20as%20per%20the%20broad%20sector%20and%20type%20of%20employment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EGraph%3A%20Real%20wages%20(in%20Rs%20at%202011%20price)%20by%20the%20sector%20and%20type%20of%20employment%2C%202018-2022%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F27093515%2FScreenshot-2024-02-27-at-9.32.35%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x969.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F27093515%2FScreenshot-2024-02-27-at-9.32.35%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x969.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F27093515%2FScreenshot-2024-02-27-at-9.32.35%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x284.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F27093515%2FScreenshot-2024-02-27-at-9.32.35%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699030%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22795%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Estimates%20by%20Santosh%20Mehrotra%20%26amp%3B%20J.%20Parida%20(forthcoming)%20and%20plot%20using%20PLFS%20unit%20level%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20will%20be%20curious%C2%A0%20to%20argue%20that%20the%20consumption%20expenditure%20would%20be%20rising%20when%20the%20real%20wages%20are%20rising%20and%20would%20be%20stagnating%20in%20the%20period%20of%20stagnant%20real%20wages%3B%20yet%20that%20is%20exactly%20what%20representatives%20of%20government%20have%20used%20HCES%202023%20data%20to%20argue.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20joblessness%20had%20already%20reached%20a%2045%20year%20high%20in%202017-18%20itself%3B%20with%20the%20continuous%20slowdown%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20joblessness%20continued%20to%20increase.%20The%20total%20number%20of%20unemployed%20was%2010%20million%202011-12%3B%20it%20rose%20to%2030%20million%20by%202018-19%2C%20bef