8.%20If%20we%20deduct%20the%20number%20of%20poor%20(94.1%20million)%20workers%20from%20this%20number%2C%20about%2057%20million%20non-poor%20workers%20live%20above%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20whose%20earning%20is%20just%20below%20Rs%20100.%20As%20per%20Tendulkar%E2%80%99s%20MRP%20line%2C%20they%20could%20still%20be%20classified%20as%20poor.%20But%20we%20are%20not%20doing%20any%20direct%20comparison%20here%20to%20avoid%20confusion.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20these%20poor%20workers%20are%20engaged%20as%20self-employed%20or%20casual%20labour.%20During%202020-21%2C%20the%20workers%20earning%20(in%20real%20terms)%20upto%20Rs%20100%20increased%20to%20204%20million.%20That%20means%20an%20additional%205%20million%20rise%20in%20vulnerable%20workforce%20only%20from%2057%20million%20to%2062%20million%2C%20because%20the%20number%20of%20poor%20workers%20increased%20massively%20during%20this%20period%20(Table%202).%20These%20facts%20imply%20that%20among%20those%20who%20were%20living%20just%20above%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20most%20of%20them%20have%20fallen%20below%20it%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20Hence%2C%20the%20number%20of%20poor%20workers%20increased%20enormously%20to%20from%2094%20million%20to%20142%20million%20between%202017-18%20and%202020-21.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20number%20of%20workers%2C%20whose%20daily%20real%20earning%20or%20wage%20is%20between%20Rs%20100%20and%20Rs%20200%20and%20between%20Rs%20200%20and%20Rs%20300%2C%20can%20also%20be%20considered%20as%20%E2%80%98poor%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98non-poor%20vulnerable%E2%80%99%20workers%2C%20respectively.%20It%20is%20noteworthy%20that%20single-bread%20winner%20families%20with%20an%20average%20family%20size%20of%204.5%20members%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20fall%20below%20the%20poverty%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20claim%20of%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20on%20growth%20being%20inclusive%20and%20broad-based%20with%20shrinking%20inequality%20%E2%80%93%20at%20the%20same%20time%20dismissing%20rural%20economic%20distress%20%E2%80%93%20must%20also%20be%20taken%20into%20perspective%20with%20the%20labour%20market%20outcomes.%20The%20number%20of%20working%20poor%20and%20the%20decline%20in%20the%20real%20wages%20indicate%20the%20need%20for%20interrogating%20the%20labour%20market%20conditions%20in%20India%2C%20before%20jumping%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20India%20has%20been%20able%20to%20end%20its%20poverty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20well%20understood%20concept%20in%20economics%20that%20with%20economic%20growth%20and%20progress%2C%20the%20share%20of%20food%20consumption%20expenditure%20in%20the%20total%20household%20expenditure%20is%20bound%20to%20come%20down.%20Food%20expenditure%20in%20total%20expenditure%20in%20rural%20households%20has%20come%20down%20from%2052.90%25%20in%202011-12%20to%2046.38%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20and%20for%20urban%20households%20from%2042.62%25%20in%202011-12%20to%2039.17%25.%20This%20must%20be%20taken%20cautiously%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20indicating%20economic%20progress.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFood%20as%20share%20of%20total%20consumer%20expenditure%20is%20just%206.4%25%20for%20USA%20(2018)%2C%206.9%25%20for%20Singapore%20(2018)%2C%207.9%25%20for%20United%20Kingdom%20(2019)%20and%208.9%25%20for%20Switzerland%20(2019).%20Our%20shares%20of%20food%20expenditure%20with%20respect%20to%20other%20developed%20countries%20remains%20high%2C%20and%20we%20have%20a%20long%20way%20till%20we%20reach%20the%20level%20of%20consumption%20expenditure%20of%20USA%20(US%20%24%2045%2C898%20per%20person%2C%202021)%20and%20Switzerland%20(US%20%24%2045%2C257%20per%20person%2C%202019).%20The%20CES%202022-23%20is%20being%20read%20to%20mean%20what%20cannot%20be%20found%20in%20it%2C%20nor%20inferred%20from%20it%20either.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESantosh%20Mehrotra%20is%20Visiting%20Professor%2C%20Center%20for%20D