ian%20foreign%20policy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20reorientation%20from%20its%20Nehruvian%20idealism%20to%20a%20more%20pragmatic%20one%20and%20his%20attempt%20to%20embed%20economic%20diplomacy%20firmly%20into%20the%20practice%20of%20Indian%20diplomacy.%20The%20policy%20change%20was%20necessitated%20by%20the%20international%20developments%20of%20the%20day%2C%20like%20the%20implosion%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20The%20foreign%20policy%20recast%20set%20India%20decisively%20on%20a%20trajectory%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmulti-alignment%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20term%20currently%20part%20of%20the%20popular%20lexicon.%20The%20start%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmulti-alignment%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20as%20we%20know%20it%20today%20%E2%80%93%20begins%20with%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20Rao%20forging%20closer%20ties%20with%20multiple%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20Israel%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20others.%20In%20fact%2C%20one%20can%20discern%20policy%20continuation%20and%20parallels%20between%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fslight-delay-but-its-okay-pv-narasimha-raos-daughter-on-his-bharat-ratna-5024838%5C%22%3ERao%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20current%20Modi%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EA%20Policy%20For%20The%20Demand%20Of%20The%20Times%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20changes%20within%20India%20that%20Rao%20initiated%20were%20in%20part%20necessitated%20by%20internal%20economic%20mismanagement%2C%20but%20equally%2C%20the%20demand%20of%20the%20times.%20The%20Berlin%20Wall%2C%20the%20dividing%20line%20between%20East%20and%20West%20Germany%2C%20came%20down%20in%201989%3B%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20collapsed%20in%201991.%20These%20events%20spelt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20leaving%20the%20US%20the%20sole%20superpower%20in%20a%20unipolar%20world.%20India%2C%20already%20battling%20economic%20challenges%2C%20saw%20a%20sharp%20trade%20slump.%20%E2%80%9CIn%201990%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20East%20European%20countries%20that%20had%20a%20rupee%20payment%20arrangement%20for%20trade%20with%20India%20accounted%20for%2017%25%20of%20India's%20total%20external%20trade.%20This%20share%20collapsed%20to%202%25%20in%201992%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20economist%20Sanjaya%20Baru%2C%20former%20media%20advisor%20to%20ex-Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20in%20his%20book%C2%A0%3Ci%3E1991%3A%20How%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20Made%20History%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(for%20the%20uninitiated%2C%20Singh%20was%20Rao's%20handpicked%20finance%20minister%20who%20implemented%20many%20of%20the%20reforms%20of%20this%20period).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVinay%20Sitapati%2C%20author%20of%C2%A0%3Ci%3EHalf%20Lion%3A%20How%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20Transformed%20India%2C%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0writes%20that%20the%20breakup%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20India%20had%20to%20rework%20its%20ties%20with%20the%20US%20and%20the%20West%20for%20the%20capital%20and%20technology%20it%20badly%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3E'State-Directed%20Capitalism'%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20practice%20of%20economic%20diplomacy%2C%20Rao%20led%20from%20the%20front.%20It's%20well%20recorded%20that%20Rao's%20first%20foreign%20visit%20soon%20after%20taking%20office%20was%20to%20Germany%2C%20the%20economic%20engine%20of%20Europe.%20Rao%20also%20led%20delegations%20to%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20in%20Davos%2C%20Switzerland%2C%20twice%2C%20to%20directly%20address%20investors%20and%20industry%20leaders.%20In%201993%2C%20he%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20to%20visit%20South%20Korea%20(borne%20out%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs'%20timeline%20of%20bilateral%20visits%20between%20the%20two).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20of%20the%20visit%20was%20to%20convince%20South%20Korean%20businesses%20to%20invest%20in%20India.%20If%20today%20Samsung%2C%20LG%2C%20Kia%20and%20Hyundai%20are%20household%20names%20in%20India%2C%20this%20is%20in%20large%20part%20due%20to%20Rao's%20efforts.%20It's%20a%20well-documented%20fact%20that%20Rao%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20meet%20the%20heads%20of%20Korean%C2%A0%3Ci%3Echaebols%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%93%20large%20family-owned%20business%20conglomerates%20%E2%80%93%20to%20explain%20how%20India%20was%20changing%20its%20economic%20focus.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20visible%20results%20was%20the%20arrival%20of%20Daewoo%20Motors%20in%20India%20in%201995%20with%20its%20range%20of%20passenger%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20imperatives%20of%20trade%20and%20economics%20dictated%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9CLook%20East%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Association%20of%20Southeast%20Asian%20Nations%20(ASEAN)%20for%20inspiration%20and%20investment.%20Sitapati%20writes%20that%20Rao%20was%20interested%20in%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstate-directed%20capitalism%E2%80%9D%20the%20Southeast%20Asian%20countries%20practised%2C%20which%20had%20allowed%20them%20to%20prosper%20economically.%20Rao%20also%20reworked%20India's%20policy%20towards%20Myanmar%20(which%20joined%20ASEAN%20in%201997).%20While%20India%20had%20supported%20freedom%20icon%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20and%20early%201990s%2C%20Rao%20understood%20that%20Myanmar%20could%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20keeping%20a%20lid%20on%20insurgency%20in%20India's%20northeast.%20Thus%20began%20India's%20engagement%20with%20the%20military%20junta.%20It%20was%20a%20policy%20borne%20out%20of%20pragmatism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EParallels%20With%20India's%20Current%20Foreign%20Strategy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20foreign%20secretary%20J.N.%20Dixit's%20book%C2%A0%3Ci%3EMy%20South%20Block%20Years%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20a%20Foreign%20Secretary%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20talks%20in%20detail%20about%20Rao%20issuing%20clear%20instructions%20to%20Indian%20diplomats%20that%20they%20needed%20to%20sell%20India's%20economic%20reforms%20to%20governments%20of%20the%20countries%20they%20were%20posted%20to.%20Ambassadors%20had%20to%20promote%20India%20as%20an%20investment%20destination.%20In%20giving%20this%20direction%20to%20diplomats%2C%20Rao%20clearly%20underlined%20that%20India's%20foreign%20policy%20and%20domestic%20economic%20policies%20were%20enmeshed.%20These%20ideas%20parallel%20those%20espoused%20and%20practised%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20today.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20business%20leaders%20were%20part%20of%20Rao's%20delegations%20abroad.%20Rao%20also%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20meet%20Indologists%20in%20countries%20he%20visited%2C%20briefing%20them%20about%20the%20developments%20in%20India.%20As%20the%20world%20began%20taking%20an%20interest%20in%20India%2C%20the%20leadership%20of%20these%20countries%20would%20first%20seek%20the%20opinions%20of%20the%20Indologists%3B%20therefore%2C%20they%20needed%20to%20be%20updated%20with%20the%20latest%20on%20India%2C%20says%20Sitapati.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EA%20Deft%20Balancing%20Act%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomic%20imperatives%20were%20high%20on%20the%20agenda%20when%20Rao%20visited%20the%20US%20in%201994.%20According%20to%20Dixit%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20acknowledged%20that%20India%2C%20having%20lost%20the%20leverage%20of%20its%20relationship%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20should%20develop%20positive%20equations%20with%20new%20power%20centres%20in%20the%20world%2C%20out%20of%20which%20the%20United%20States%20was%20the%20most%20important%20one.%E2%80%9D%20Rao%20was%20clear%20that%20India's%20fundamental%20interests%20%E2%80%94%20on%20nuclear%20non-proliferation%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20would%20not%20be%20compromised%20as%20it%20looked%20to%20forge%20new%20economic%2C%20technology%20and%20defence%20partnerships%20with%20the%20US%20%E2%80%9Cto%20the%20extent%20feasible%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20India%20was%20almost%20completely%20dependent%20on%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20for%20military%20hardware%2C%20a%20defence%20partnership%20with%20the%20US%20was%20definitely%20a%20novel%20concept.%20It%20was%20only%20after%20the%20year%202000%20that%20US-India%20defence%20trade%20picked%20up%3B%20today%20India%20has%20many%20US-made%20platforms%20in%20its%20defence%20inventory%20and%20there%20are%20plans%20for%20joint%20production%2C%20besides%20the%20transfer%20of%20fighter%20jet%20engine%20technology%20%E2%80%93%20something%20inconceivable%20during%20the%20Rao%20years.%20Dixit%20writes%20that%20Rao%20wanted%20the%20Indian-American%20population%20leveraged%20to%20create%20a%20favourable%20opinion%20of%20India%20in%20the%20US%20among%20businesses%20and%20lawmakers.%20This%20is%20something%20the%20Vajpayee%20government%20successfully%20did%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20India's%20nuclear%20tests%20in%201998%20and%20something%20commonplace%20in%20diplomatic%20practice%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EReshaping%20Ties%20With%20Israel%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreceding%20Rao's%20US%20sojourn%2C%20India%20normalised%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20While%20India%20was%20looking%20to%20forge%20ties%20with%20the%20US%2C%20New%20Delhi's%20new%20outlook%20towards%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20advertised%2C%20Sitapati%20says%20in%20his%20book.%20This%20is%20where%20reshaping%20ties%20with%20Israel%20(which%20has%20close%20relations%20with%20the%20US)%20came%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20India%20had%20solidly%20stood%20by%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20shunning%20formal%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20In%201991%2C%20in%20a%20first%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20UN%20resolution%20reversing%20the%20equation%20of%20Zionism%20with%20racism%E2%80%94something%20the%20US%20noticed%2C%20says%20Sitapati.%20In%20a%20parallel%20move%2C%20Rao%20also%20worked%20to%20convince%20Palestinian%20leader%20Yasser%20Arafat%20that%20Indian%20ties%20with%20Israel%20would%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20push%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%20Arafat%20did%20not%20object%20to%20the%20exchange%20of%20ambassadors.%20Another%20imperative%20for%20normalising%20ties%20with%20Israel%20was%20defence.%20The%20disintegration%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20meant%20India's%20reliable%20supplier%20of%20military%20equipment%20did%20not%20exist.%20And%20New%20Delhi%20had%20to%20look%20for%20newer%20options.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERao's%20moves%20were%20to%20help%20India%20on%20this%20count%20too.%20In%20Parliament%2C%20Rao%20justified%20the%20formalisation%20of%20ties%20with%20Israel%20as%20a%20continuation%20of%20existing%20policy%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20India%20already%20had%20an%20Israeli%20consulate%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20dating%20back%20to%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru's%20time.%20This%20blunted%20criticism%20from%20within%20his%20own%20Congress%20Party.%20Today%2C%20India%20and%20Israel%20enjoy%20a%20very%20close%20strategic%20partnership%20and%20India%20imports%20large%20quantities%20of%20military%20hardware%20from%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EEngaging%20With%20West%20Asia%20To%20Counter%20Pakistan%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMindful%20of%20the%20complexities%20of%20West%20Asian%20politics%2C%20Rao%20visited%20Iran%20in%201993%2C%20a%20year%20after%20India%20established%20formal%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20India's%20Iran%20outreach%20was%20important%20to%20counter%20Pakistan%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Kashmir%20dispute%20was%20smouldering.%20In%201995%2C%20India%20played%20host%20to%20then-Iranian%20leader%20Ali%20Akbar%20Hashemi%20Rafsanjani%20%E2%80%93%20a%20signal%20that%20India%20under%20Rao%20had%20successfully%20managed%20to%20balance%20ties%20between%20Israel%20and%20Iran%20and%20also%20the%20wider%20West%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuilding%20ties%20with%20the%20US%20did%20not%20mean%20disregarding%20Russia.%20Rao%20ensured%20open%20lines%20of%20communication%20with%20the%20new%20Russian%20president%20Boris%20Yeltsin%20given%20India's%20dependence%20on%20Moscow%20for%20a%20range%20of%20defence%20equipment%20and%20trade.%20But%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20India's%20ties%20with%20the%20new%20Russian%20Federation%20would%20be%20qualitatively%20different%20from%20the%20past.%20Russian%20dependence%20on%20the%20West%20for%20capital%20and%20investment%20meant%20that%20traditional%20Russian%20support%20for%20issues%20like%20non-proliferation%20and%20Kashmir%20would%20be%20impacted%20by%20the%20West.%20This%20was%20something%20new%20for%20India%20that%20Rao%20and%20his%20team%20had%20to%20manage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Nuclear%20Tests%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20recounting%20all%20the%20novel%20firsts%20of%20the%20Rao%20years%20in%20office%2C%20it%20would%20be%20remiss%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20preparations%20for%20a%20nuclear%20test%20made%20under%20his%20watch.%20According%20to%20various%20reports%2C%20Rao%20had%20given%20scientists%20the%20go-ahead%20for%20the%20test%20but%20deferred%20it%20after%20US%20spy%20satellites%20detected%20activity%20at%20the%20test%20site.%20Other%20reports%20suggest%20that%20Rao%20would%20have%20done%20the%20tests%20had%20he%20won%20the%201996%20elections.%20As%20it%20stands%2C%20the%20Congress%20party%20lost%20the%201996%20polls%2C%20and%20when%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20came%20to%20power%20in%201998%2C%20the%20Vajpayee%20government%20conducted%20the%20tests.%20India%20needed%20to%20test%20its%20nuclear%20weapons'%20capabilities%20as%20it%20was%20coming%20under%20international%20pressure%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%20and%20sign%20the%20Comprehensive%20Test%20Ban%20Treaty%2C%20which%20would%20squeeze%20India's%20nuclear%20options.%20In%20India's%20immediate%20neighbourhood%20at%20that%20time%2C%20Pakistan%20was%20believed%20to%20have%20nuclear%20weapons%3B%20China%20definitely%20did%2C%20too.%20Bordered%20on%20two%20sides%20by%20nuclear-armed%20countries%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20na%C3%AFve%20and%20foolhardy%20on%20India's%20part%20not%20to%20have%20readied%20itself%20for%20a%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rao%20years%20saw%20Pakistan-sponsored%20terrorism%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20peak.%20It%20was%20also%20a%20time%20peppered%20with%20multiple%20Pakistani%20attempts%20to%20focus%20the%20international%20spotlight%20on%20India's%20alleged%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20Kashmir.%20Rao%20devised%20a%20novel%20approach%20to%20meet%20this%20challenge.%20In%20March%201994%2C%20India%20was%20in%20the%20dock%20at%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20in%20Geneva%3B%20Rao%20put%20together%20a%20team%20of%20then-opposition%20BJP%20leader%20Atal%20Behari%20Vajpayee%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20leader%20Farooq%20Abdullah%20and%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20external%20affairs%2C%20Salman%20Khurshid%2C%20to%20represent%20India.%20The%20strategy%20worked%20and%20the%20Pakistani%20resolution%20was%20not%20carried%20through.%20One%20has%20to%20credit%20Rao%20for%20his%20political%20sagacity%20in%20putting%20together%20such%20a%20team%20at%20such%20a%20critical%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20Rao%20Dealt%20With%20China%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20China%2C%20Rao%20oversaw%20the%20signing%20of%20a%20key%20agreement%20with%20Beijing%20%E2%80%94%20the%20agreement%20on%20the%20Maintenance%20of%20Peace%20and%20Tranquility%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20on%20the%20Sino-Indian%20Border%20in%201993.%20It%20built%20upon%20the%20momentum%20generated%20by%20the%201988%20visit%20to%20China%20by%20then-Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%20With%20the%20ties%20with%20China%20currently%20in%20the%20freezer%2C%20one%20might%20choose%20to%20devalue%20the%201993%20pact.%20But%20consider%20this%3A%20the%20Indian%20economy%20was%20weak%2C%20the%20country%20had%20few%20friends%20compared%20to%20today%2C%20and%20it%20was%20beset%20with%20terrorism%20challenges%20posed%20by%20Pakistan.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20it%20was%20vitally%20important%20that%20India%20have%20peace%20along%20its%20northern%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20%E2%80%9Crebalancing%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cre-ordering%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20global%20order%20are%20buzzwords%20today%2C%20they%20were%20as%20much%20the%20reality%20of%20the%201990s.%20Rao%20and%20his%20team%20%E2%80%93%20Manmohan%20Singh%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20economy%20and%20J.N.%20Dixit%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20foreign%20policy%20%E2%80%93%20ably%20steered%20India%20through%20the%20tough%20times.%20If%20India%20is%20able%20to%20manoeuvre%20through%20rough%20times%20today%2C%20some%20credit%20needs%20to%20go%20to%20Rao%2C%20who%20set%20India%20on%20this%20course%20economically%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20foreign%20policy%2C%20with%20a%20pair%20of%20steady%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Elizabeth%20Roche%20is%20Associate%20Professor%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20International%20Affairs%2C%20OP%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%C2%A0Sonipat)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709003520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fqmvi387g_pv-narasimha-rao_625x300_09_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnarasimha-rao-recast-not-just-indias-economy-but-foreign-policy-too-5134659%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20India%20is%20able%20to%20manoeuvre%20through%20rough%20times%20today%2C%20some%20credit%20needs%20to%20go%20to%20Rao%2C%20who%20set%20India%20on%20this%20course%20economically%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20foreign%20policy%2C%20with%20a%20pair%20of%20steady%20hands.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnarasimha-rao-recast-not-just-indias-economy-but-foreign-policy-too-5134659%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnarasimha-rao-recast-not-just-indias-economy-but-foreign-policy-too-5134659%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fnarasimha-rao-recast-not-just-indias-economy-but-foreign-policy-too-5134659%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%2