an%205%2C000%20satellites%2C%20provides%20broadband%20to%20parts%20of%20Earth%20and%20has%20achieved%20cash%20flow%20break-even%2C%20according%20to%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EROCKET%20LAB%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERocket%20Lab%20was%20founded%20in%202006%20by%20New%20Zealander%20Peter%20Beck%20and%20went%20public%20in%20the%20U.S.%20in%202021%20through%20a%20merger%20with%20a%20special%20purpose%20acquisition%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20consider%20it%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20more%20promising%20%26quot%3BNew%20Space%26quot%3B%20companies%20as%20it%20is%20the%20most%20frequent%20private%20launcher%20of%20rockets%20after%20SpaceX.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20known%20for%20launching%20satellites%20into%20niche%20orbits%20on%20its%20Electron%20small%20rocket%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20test%20its%20reusable%20Neutron%20rocket%20later%20this%20year.%20The%20rocket%20is%20designed%20to%20be%20able%20to%20deliver%20a%20large%20number%20of%20satellite%20to%20low%20Earth%20orbit%20and%20even%20enable%20missions%20to%20Mars%20and%20Venus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERocket%20Lab%20has%20several%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20federal%20contracts%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20including%20production%20of%20satellites%2C%20launch%20of%20spacecraft%20and%20a%20deal%20to%20explore%20delivering%20cargo%20around%20the%20world%20using%20its%20rockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBLUE%20ORIGIN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlue%20Origin%2C%20the%20aerospace%20company%20founded%20by%20billionaire%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20has%20been%20selected%20by%20NASA%20to%20develop%20its%20Blue%20Moon%20human%20landing%20system%20for%20the%20Artemis%20V%20mission%20at%20a%20total%20contract%20value%20of%20%243.4%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20last%20year%20also%20awarded%20Blue%20Origin%20%2435%20million%20to%20advance%20its%20Blue%20Alchemist%20technology%20to%20autonomously%20make%20solar%20cells%20and%20oxygen%20from%20moon%20dust%20and%20crushed%20rock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20competes%20with%20British%20business%20tycoon%20Richard%20Branson's%20Virgin%20Galactic%20for%20space%20tourism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFIREFLY%20AEROSPACE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20based%20in%20Cedar%20Park%2C%20Texas%2C%20is%20working%20on%20a%20lander%20named%20Blue%20Ghost%20to%20deliver%20private%20and%20government%20payloads%20to%20the%20moon%20this%20year%2C%20including%20three%20under%20the%20CLPS%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirefly%2C%20backed%20by%20AE%20Industrial%20Partners%2C%20is%20trying%20to%20mass-produce%20its%20medium-sized%20rocket%2C%20while%20developing%20the%20first%20stage%20for%20Northrop's%20all-American%20version%20of%20Antares%20rocket%2C%20announced%20in%20August%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20the%20company%20was%20chosen%20to%20be%20the%20launch%20provider%20by%20the%20National%20Reconnaissance%20Office%20for%20a%2010-year%20long%20contract%20with%20a%20value%20of%20up%20to%20%24700%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20was%20valued%20at%20%241.5%20billion%20late%20last%20year%2C%20after%20raising%20about%20%24300%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708999260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fo2v1mfh_us-moon-lander_625x300_27_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspacex-to-blue-origin-moon-landing-puts-space-race-startups-in-spotlight-5132776%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Interest%20in%20space%20startups%20has%20spiked%20after%20Intuitive%20Machines%20became%20the%20first%20private%20firm%20to%20successfully%20land%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20in%20the%20first%20U.S.%20touchdown%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20in%20more%20than%20half%2