lunar%20lander%20that%20tipped%20over%20during%20touchdown%20has%20sent%20back%20its%20first%20images%20from%20the%20farthest%20south%20any%20vessel%20has%20ever%20landed%20on%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20uncrewed%20Odysseus%2C%20built%20by%20Houston-based%20Intuitive%20Machines%2C%20returned%20the%20United%20States%20to%20Earth's%20cosmic%20neighbor%20last%20week%20after%20a%20five-decade%20absence%2C%20in%20a%20first%20for%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20of%20its%20legs%20caught%20on%20the%20surface%20as%20it%20came%20down%2C%20making%20it%20pitch%20over%20in%20the%20final%20act%20of%20a%20drama-packed%20journey%20that%20was%20saved%20by%20an%20improvised%20fix.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOdysseus%20continues%20to%20communicate%20with%20flight%20controllers%20in%20Nova%20Control%20from%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%26quot%3B%20Intuitive%20Machines%20said%20Monday%20in%20an%20update%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20included%20two%20pictures%3A%20one%20from%20the%20hexagon-shaped%20spaceship's%20descent%2C%20and%20the%20other%20taken%2035%20seconds%20after%20it%20fell%20over%2C%20revealing%20the%20pockmarked%20soil%20of%20the%20Malapert%20A%20impact%20crater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EOdysseus%20captured%20this%20image%20approximately%2035%20seconds%20after%20pitching%20over%20during%20its%20approach%20to%20the%20landing%20site.%20The%20camera%20is%20on%20the%20starboard%20aft-side%20of%20the%20lander%20in%20this%20phase.%202%2F5%20(26FEB2024%200745%20CST)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FoUcjk3bCqW%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FoUcjk3bCqW%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Intuitive%20Machines%20(%40Int_Machines)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FInt_Machines%2Fstatus%2F1762111939142885816%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2026%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20is%20planning%20to%20return%20astronauts%20to%20the%20Moon%20later%20this%20decade%2C%20and%20paid%20Intuitive%20Machines%20around%20%24120%20million%20for%20the%20mission%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20new%20initiative%20to%20delegate%20cargo%20missions%20to%20the%20private%20sector%20and%20stimulate%20a%20commercial%20lunar%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOdysseus%20carries%20a%20suite%20of%20NASA%20instruments%20designed%20to%20improve%20scientific%20understanding%20of%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole%2C%20where%20the%20space%20agency%20plans%20to%20send%20astronauts%20under%20its%20Artemis%20program%20later%20this%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20during%20Apollo%2C%20the%20plan%20is%20to%20build%20long-term%20habitats%2C%20harvesting%20polar%20ice%20for%20drinking%20water%20and%20for%20rocket%20fuel%20for%20onward%20missions%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Lunar%20Reconnaissance%20Orbiter%20(LRO)%20probe%20meanwhile%20photographed%20the%204.0-meter%20(13%20feet)%20tall%20%26quot%3BNova-C%26quot%3B%20class%20lander%20on%20Saturday%20at%20a%20spot%20within%201.5%20kilometers%20(a%20mile)%20of%20its%20intended%20landing%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EFlight%20controllers%20intend%20to%20collect%20data%20until%20the%20lander's%20solar%20panels%20are%20no%20longer%20exposed%20to%20light.%20Based%20on%20Earth%20and%20Moon%20positioning%2C%20we%20believe%20flight%20controllers%20will%20continue%20to%20communicate%20with%20Odysseus%20until%20Tuesday%20morning.%20Image%20credit%3A%20NASA%2FGoddard%2FArizona%20State%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFFt8CXZPIC%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FFFt8CXZPIC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Intuitive%20Machines%20(%40Int_Machines)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FInt_Machines%2Fstatus%2F1762111945291755652%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2026%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20student%20team%20behind%20an%20external%20camera%20that%20was%20initially%20meant%20to%20shoot%20out%20from%20Odysseus%20during%20its%20descent%20said%20in%20a%20weekend%20update%20they%20remained%20%26quot%3Boptimistic%26quot%3B%20EagleCam%20could%20still%20be%20ejected%20from%20the%20fallen%20lander%20and%20snap%20photos%20from%20around%20four%20meters%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAstronomer%20and%20space%20missions%20expert%20Jonathan%20McDowell%20told%20AFP%20the%20fact%20that%20Odysseus%20was%20lying%20on%20its%20side%20didn't%20overly%20concern%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuccess%20with%20minor%20footnotes%20--%20I'd%20give%20it%20an%20A%20minus%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20one%20would%20%26quot%3Bprefer%20it%20to%20be%20upright%2C%20and%20they've%20certainly%20got%20some%20things%20to%20figure%20out%20for%20future%20missions%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20overall%20things%20are%20moving%20in%20the%20right%20direction%20for%20NASA's%20Commercial%20Lunar%20Payload%20Services%20(CLPS)%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Intuitive%20Machines%20revealed%20its%20engineers%20had%20forgotten%20to%20toggle%20a%20safety%20switch%20that%20prevented%20the%20spaceship's%20laser-guided%20landing%20system%20from%20engaging%2C%20which%20forced%20them%20to%20upload%20a%20software%20patch%20and%20rely%20on%20an%20experimental%20NASA%20system%20to%20save%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRocket%20science%20is%20hard%20not%20because%20any%20one%20thing%20is%20super%20hard%2C%20but%20because%20you%20have%20to%20do%20a%20million%20easy%20things%20all%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McDowell%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bembarrassing%26quot%3B%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlight%20controllers%20will%20continue%20to%20download%20data%20until%20the%20lander's%20solar%20panels%20are%20no%20longer%20exposed%20to%20light%2C%20which%20is%20now%20estimated%20to%20be%20Tuesday%20morning%2C%20said%20Intuitive%20Machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20slightly%20shorter%20mission%20duration%20than%20initially%20planned%2C%20likely%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20spacecraft's%20awkward%20orientation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan's%20space%20agency%20also%20landed%20a%20spaceship%20wonkily%20on%20the%20Moon%20last%20month%2C%20but%20produced%20a%20surprise%20on%20Monday%20by%20waking%20up%20its%20SLIM%20lander%20following%20the%20lunar%20night%2C%20which%20lasts%20around%20two%20Earth%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMcDowell%20said%20the%20two%20falls%20might%20indicate%20the%20current%20generation%20of%20landers%20are%20too%20top%20heavy%20and%20consequently%20tip%20over%20too%20easily%20in%20low%20gravity%2C%20unlike%20the%20short%2C%20squat%20landers%20with%20splayed%20legs%20built%20by%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Soviet%20Union%20during%20the%20Cold%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntuitive%20Machines%20joined%20an%20exclusive%20club%20of%20five%20countries%20that%20have%20achieved%20soft%20lunar%20landings%3A%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20China%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Japan.%20Three%20prior%20private%20attempts%20failed%2C%20including%20by%20another%20American%20company%2C%20Astrobotic%2C%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708977660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F23mccn5o_odysseus-moon-images_625x300_27_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fodysseus-intuitive-machines-us-spaceship-lying-sideways-on-lunar-surface-shares-first-images-from-moon-5133407%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20American%20lunar%20lander%20that%20tipped%20over%20during%20touchdown%20has%20sent%20back%20its%20first%20images%20from%20the%20farthest%20south%20any%20vessel%20has%20ever%20landed%20on%20the%20Moon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22