hat%20they%20say%20is%20the%20increasing%20unsustainability%20of%20their%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A237%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbrussels-angry-farmers-launch-manure-and-eggs-at-police-near-eu-meeting-in-latest-protest-13081606%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbrussels-angry-farmers-launch-manure-and-eggs-at-police-near-eu-meeting-in-latest-protest-13081606%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbrussels-angry-farmers-launch-manure-and-eggs-at-police-near-eu-meeting-in-latest-protest-13081606%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Allahabad%20HC%20Rules%20in%20Favour%20of%20Continuation%20of%20Hindu%20Prayers%20at%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque's%20Basement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20citizen%20right%20guaranteed%20under%20Article%2025%20of%20the%20constitution%20(freedom%20of%20religion)%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20be%20taken%20away%20by%20arbitrary%20action%20of%20state%E2%80%9D%2C%20noted%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20on%20Monday%2C%20February%2026%2C%20as%20it%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20continuation%20of%20Hindu%20prayers%20in%20the%20basement%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20in%20Varanasi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20dismissed%20a%20plea%20filed%20by%20the%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%20challenging%20a%20controversial%20district%20court%20order%20handing%20over%20a%20southern%20cellar%20of%20the%20Mughal-era%20Muslim%20place%20of%20worship%20to%20Hindus%20for%20worship%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20pending%20suits%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjd%20%E2%80%93%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20matter%20in%20which%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20are%20seeking%20religious%20rights%20within%20the%20mosque%20as%20well%20as%20its%20ultimate%20possession%20from%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20eventually%20boiled%20down%20to%20which%20party%20%E2%80%93%20the%20mosque%20management%20committee%20or%20a%20Hindu%20plaintiff%20%E2%80%93%20could%20prove%20possession%20of%20the%20southern%20cellar%20before%20it%20was%20locked%20in%201993.%20A%20map%20from%20a%20civil%20suit%20in%201936%20and%20an%20advocate%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20survey%20report%20of%20the%20mosque%20in%201996%20were%20judged%20by%20the%20HC%20to%20be%20evidence%20sufficient%20to%20prove%20that%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiff%20had%20prima%20facie%20possession%20of%20the%20basement%20of%20the%20mosque%20till%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20held%20that%20the%20Muslim%20side%20had%20failed%20to%20establish%20prima%20facie%20possession%20over%20the%20cellar%20when%20the%20property%20was%20iron-fenced%20and%20barricaded%20in%201993%2C%20on%20the%20directions%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20following%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20state%20government%2C%20then%20run%20by%20the%20Mulayam%20Singh-led%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20had%20stopped%20the%20worship%20and%20Hindu%20rituals%20in%20the%20cellar%20of%20the%20mosque%20by%20the%20Vyas%20family%2C%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%2C%20%E2%80%9Cby%20illegal%20action%20of%20State%20without%20there%20being%20any%20order%20in%20writing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFailure%20of%20appellant%20(Muslims)%20to%20establish%20prima%20facie%20possession%20over%20the%20disputed%20property%20(basement)%2C%20and%20plaintiff%20(Vyas%20family)%20succeeding%20in%20building%20up%20a%20strong%20prima%20facie%20case%20negating%20the%20stand%20of%20appellant%2C%20leads%20to%20undeniable%20situation%20that%20stopping%20worship%20and%20performance%20of%20rituals%20by%20the%20devotees%20in%20the%20cellar%20would%20be%20against%20their%20interest%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20Justice%20Rohit%20Ranjan%20Agarwal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDistrict%20judge%20A.%20K%20Vishvesha%20had%20on%20January%2031%2C%20his%20last%20day%20of%20work%20before%20retirement%2C%20directed%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20make%20arrangements%20for%20puja%20and%20other%20Hindu%20activities%20inside%20the%20southern%20tehkhana%20of%20the%20mosque%20within%20seven%20days.%20The%20district%20court%20order%20was%20passed%20on%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20a%20local%20priest%20Shailendra%20Kumar%20Pathak%20of%20the%20Acharya%20Ved%20Vyas%20Peeth%20temple%2C%20who%20had%20sought%20rights%20to%20worship%20the%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20and%20other%20alleged%20visible%20and%20invisible%20deities%20he%20claimed%20were%20in%20the%20cellar%20of%20the%20mosque.%20The%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%20had%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20all%20claims%20made%20by%20Pathak%20that%20there%20were%20idols%20kept%20inside%20the%20previously-sealed%20cellar%20and%20that%20his%20ancestors%20used%20to%20carry%20out%20puja%20inside%20the%20cellar.%20They%20challenged%20the%20order%20and%20its%20hasty%20execution%20by%20the%20district%20administration%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20on%20February%201%20in%20the%20HC%20and%20demanded%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20puja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2026%2C%20Justice%20Agarwal%20ruled%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20strong%20prima%20facie%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20of%20possession%20of%20the%20cellar%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Vyas%20family%20from%20the%20British%20era%20till%201993.%C2%A0%20Justice%20Agarwal%20held%20that%20allowing%20worship%20and%20rituals%20in%20the%20basement%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20the%20receiver%20(district%20magistrate)%20appointed%20by%20the%20lower%20court%20required%20no%20interference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPrima%20facie%20I%20find%20that%20act%20of%20the%20State%20Government%20since%20year%201993%20restraining%20Vyas%20family%20from%20performing%20religious%20worship%20and%20rituals%20and%20also%20by%20the%20devotees%20was%20a%20continues%20wrong%20being%20perpetuated%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Justice%20Agarwal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20observed%20that%20the%20Vyas%20family%20%E2%80%9Cwho%20continued%20performance%20of%20religious%20worship%20and%20rituals%20in%20the%20cellar%20could%20not%20be%20denied%20access%20by%20oral%20order.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Agarwal%20dismissed%20the%20appeals%20filed%20by%20the%20management%20committee%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Chad%20not%20made%20out%20any%20case%20for%20interfering%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20district%20court%20orders%20of%20January%2017%20and%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20court%20had%20on%20January%2017%2C%20on%20an%20application%20by%20Pathak%2C%20appointed%20the%20district%20magistrate%20as%20the%20receiver%20of%20the%20basement%20and%20directed%20him%20to%20keep%20it%20secure.%20On%20January%2024%2C%20the%20basement%20was%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20district%20administration.%20A%20week%20later%2C%20the%20district%20court%20amended%20its%20order%20and%20issued%20a%20fresh%20direction%20to%20the%20district%20administration%20to%20make%20arrangements%20for%20puja%20and%20other%20Hindu%20activities%20inside%20the%20southern%20tehkhana%20of%20the%C2%A0mosque%C2%A0and%20conduct%20the%20puja%20and%20%E2%80%9Crag-bhog%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cidols%E2%80%9D%20inside%20the%20tehkhana%20through%20a%20pujari%20appointed%20by%20the%20Shri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Varanasi%C2%A0court%C2%A0order%20came%20days%20after%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20in%20its%20survey%20report%20claimed%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20Hindu%20temple%E2%80%9D%20existed%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20prior%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20existing%20structure%20i.e%20the%C2%A0mosque%C2%A0and%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20temple%20were%20modified%20and%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Islamic%20place%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20overruled%20objections%20raised%20by%20the%20lawyers%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20management%20committee%20and%20said%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20illegality%20or%20mistake%20committed%20by%20the%E2%80%9D%20district%20judge%20while%20appointing%20the%20district%20magistrate%20as%20the%20receiver%20for%20the%20basement%20and%20issuing%20directions%20for%20arranging%20worship%20there.%20The%20appointment%20of%20the%20receiver%20%E2%80%9Cin%20no%20way%20affects%20the%20right%20or%20title%20of%20any%20of%20the%20party%20during%20pendency%20of%20the%20suit%20as%20Receiver%20is%20appointed%20to%20protect%20the%20property%20being%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20Court%20and%20of%20all%20the%20parties%20interested%20in%20litigation.%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20HC%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20management%20committee%20lawyer%20SFA%20Naqvi%20argued%20that%20the%20district%20court%20could%20not%20have%20passed%20the%20January%2017%20order%20appointing%20the%20receiver%20and%20that%20the%20order%20appointing%20him%20was%20in%20teeth%20of%20the%20directions%20passed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%201993%2C%201995%20and%201997%20directing%20protection%20of%20the%20mosque%20following%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition%20of%20December%206%2C%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20management%20committee%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20a%201937%20lower%20court%20order%20to%20show%20possession%20of%20the%20basement%20seemed%20to%20backfire%20on%20them%2C%20as%20Justice%20Agarwal%20interpreted%20that%20the%20same%20case%20had%20validated%20the%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs.%20A%20map%20from%201936%20and%20a%20Commissioner%E2%80%99s%20report%20of%201996%20together%20not%20only%20negated%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20Masjid%20management%20committee%E2%80%99s%20plea%20regarding%20possession%20of%20the%20basement%20but%20also%20%E2%80%9Cadvances%20prima%20facie%20evidence%20of%20possession%20in%20favour%20of%20predecessors%20of%20plaintiff%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20of%20Management%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%2C%20the%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20had%20argued%20in%20court%20that%20the%20property%20had%20been%20declared%20a%20mosque%20and%20the%20courtyard%20with%20the%20land%20underneath%20as%20Hanafi%20Muslim%20Waqf%20by%20an%20additional%20civil%20judge%20in%201937%20in%20the%20Din%20Mohammad%20suit%20case%20filed%20in%201936.%20The%20Anujuman%20argued%20that%20in%20view%20of%20the%201937%20court%20decision%2C%20the%20Vyas%20family%20no%20longer%20had%20any%20right%20over%20the%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaqvi%20said%20that%20the%20Din%20Mohammad%20case%20judgment%20had%20already%20settled%20the%20question%20regarding%20the%20mosque%20and%20its%20courtyard%20with%20the%20land%20underneath%2C%20as%20being%20Hanafi%20Waqf%20land.%20Once%20the%20cellar%20has%20been%20declared%20as%20Hanafi%20Muslim%20Waqf%2C%20the%20application%20filed%20by%20Pathak%20could%20not%20have%20been%20entertained%20and%20the%20receiver%20could%20not%20have%20been%20appointed%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Naqvi%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20position%20was%20settled%2C%20any%20claim%20seeking%20relief%20regarding%20the%20land%20underneath%20it%20had%20to%20be%20decided%20in%20a%20proper%20suit%20and%20not%20by%20interim%20orders%2C%20Naqvi%20further%20said%2C%20objecting%20to%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20district%20court%20entertained%20Pathak%E2%80%99s%20suit%20after%20a%20delay%20of%2031%20years%20without%20any%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20a%20map%20filed%20in%20the%201936%20Din%20Mohammad%20suit%20by%20the%20state%20(defendant)%20was%20admitted%20by%20the%20court%20against%20the%20plaintiff%20Din%20Mohammad%20on%20May%2014%2C%201937%2C%20wherein%20the%20basement%20owned%20by%20the%20Vyas%20family%20has%20been%20shown.%20This%20showed%20that%20the%20court%20in%201937%20admitted%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20Vyas%20family%20and%20the%20cellar%20owned%20by%20them%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20existence%20of%20Vyas%20tehkhana%20(cellar)%20owned%20by%20Vyas%20family%20in%20the%20year%201937%20is%20a%20prima%20facie%20proof%20of%20the%20continued%20possession%20claimed%20by%20the%20plaintiff%20till%20the%20year%201993%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Agarwal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%201937%20judgment%2C%20from%20which%20case%20the%20masjid%20committee%20was%20deleted%20from%20the%20array%20of%20parties%2C%20relied%20upon%20by%20the%20Masjid%20management%20committee%20%E2%80%9Cactually%20helps%20the%20case%20of%20the%20plaintiff%20as%20not%20only%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20trial%20has%20been%20made%20out%2C%20but%20also%20the%20balance%20of%20convenience%20tilts%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20plaintiff%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Agarwal%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20the%20Masjid%20management%20committee%20did%20not%20claim%20the%20basement%20at%20any%20point%20from%20the%20Vyas%20family%20after%201937%20till%20December%201993%20leads%20%E2%80%9Cto%20adverse%20inference%E2%80%9D%20against%20it%20regarding%20the%20possession%2C%20Justice%20Agarwal%20concluded.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiff%20was%20successful%20in%20%E2%80%9Cprima%20facie%20establishing%E2%80%9D%20their%20possession%20through%20the%20Vyas%20family%20since%201551%2C%20the%20court%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20admitted%20the%20July%2030%2C%201996%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20report%20filed%20in%20a%20civil%20suit%20in%20a%20local%20court%20in%20Varanasi%20as%20proof%20that%20demonstrates%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpresence%20of%20lock%E2%80%9D%20put%20up%20on%20the%20gate%20of%20the%20basement%20by%20the%20predecessors%20of%20Pathak%2C%20providing%20%E2%80%9Ca%20strong%20prima%20facie%20evidence%20of%20possession.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20mentioned%20that%20two%20locks%20were%20put%20on%20the%20western%20side%20of%20the%20basement%2C%20one%20by%20the%20district%20administration%20and%20another%20by%20Somnath%20Vyas%2C%20Pathak%E2%80%99s%20grandfather%2C%20who%20was%20also%20the%20one%20who%20filed%20the%20original%20suit%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20matter%20seeking%20claim%20over%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708956941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fallahabad-hc-rules-in-favour-of-continuation-of-hindu-prayers-at-gyanvapi-mosques-basement%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20dismissed%20a%20plea%20filed%20by%20the%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%20challenging%20a%20controversial%20district%20court%20order%20handing%20over%20a%20southern%20cellar%20of%20the%20Mughal-era%20Muslim%20place%20of%20worship%20to%20Hindus%20for%20worship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fallahabad-hc-rules-in-favour-of-continuation-of-hindu-prayers-at-gyanvapi-mosques-basement%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CBI%20court%20convicts%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20manager%20after%2027%20years%20of%20chargesheet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708956494000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F11%2Ffull%2F1691761580-9723.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcbi-court-convicts-bank-of-baroda-manager-after-27-years-of-chargesheet-124022600911_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20central%20probe%20agency%20had%20taken%20over%20the%20probe%20in%201994%20and%20had%20filed%20a%20charge%20sheet%20in%20both%20cases%20in%201996%2C%20CBI%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fn