0in%20the%20air%3A%20time%2C%20then%2C%20to%20make%20a%20radical%20film.%20What%20he%20did%20do%2C%20when%20he%20got%20the%20chance%2C%20was%20to%20make%20a%20film%20that%20defied%20one%E2%80%99s%20understanding%20of%20the%20radical%20gesture.%20%3Cem%3EMaya%20Darpan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20was%20called%3A%20a%20slow%2C%20slow%2C%20saga%20of%20a%20woman%20whose%20inner%20traumas%20mapped%20onto%20the%20world%3A%20a%20desert%20landscape%20from%20which%20she%20would%20occasionally%20depart%20in%20the%20fantasies%20of%20luxurious%20green%20foliage%2C%20a%20%3Cem%3Efinale%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20Chhau%20dance%20and%20a%20tilting%20camera.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%2C%20it%20was%20said%2C%20was%20unreleasable.%20It%20was%20widely%20attacked%20%E2%80%93%20among%20others%2C%20by%20Satyajit%20Ray%2C%20who%20accused%20it%20of%20threatening%20film%20language%20with%20extinction.%20%3Cem%3EMaya%20Darpan%3C%2Fem%3E%20survived%20however%2C%20and%20even%20grew%20and%20changed%2C%20seen%20by%20viewers%20in%20India%20and%20elsewhere%20in%20numbers%20exceeding%20the%20viewers%20of%20most%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98art%20cinema%20with%20a%20commercial%20edge%E2%80%99%20that%20many%20were%20making%20at%20the%20time.%20Problem%20was%2C%20there%20was%20no%20way%20of%20commoditising%20the%20kind%20of%20value%20his%20cinema%20represented%3A%20a%20problem%20with%20which%20he%20was%20familiar%2C%20as%20would%20have%20been%20his%20teacher%2C%20D.D.%20Kosambi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20Shahani%20was%20said%20to%20have%20been%20uncompromising.%20That%2C%20if%20any%2C%20was%20the%20word%20that%20famously%20defined%20him.%20He%20put%20India%20to%20the%20test%2C%20both%20in%20the%20films%20he%20actually%20made%2C%20and%20more%20in%20the%20ones%20he%20could%20not%20make.%20In%20both%2C%20he%20transformed%2C%20and%20eventually%20owned%2C%20the%20famous%20question%2C%20what%20is%20cinema%20in%20an%20India%20that%20has%20been%20confusing%20to%20historians%2C%20economists%20and%20cultural%20theorists%20alike.%20What%20defined%20India%3F%20Could%20this%20be%20captured%20in%20narrative%20practices%20at%20all%2C%20and%20if%20so%20what%20might%20such%20practices%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26155002%2FDSC_3925-SS.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26155002%2FDSC_3925-SS.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26155002%2FDSC_3925-SS-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26155002%2FDSC_3925-SS-1024x684.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698934%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAlaknanda%20Samarth%20as%20the%20sphynx%20in%20Khayal%20Gatha%20(1989).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20clear%20that%20music%20had%20something%20to%20say%20to%20this%2C%20especially%20forms%20that%20arose%20as%20much%20through%20improvised%20means%2C%20the%20better%20he%20said%20to%20evade%20hierarchical%20order.%20Answers%2C%20if%20we%20could%20use%20the%20word%2C%20were%20to%20be%20found%20in%20the%20most%20unexpected%20of%20places%2C%20on%20street%20corners%20as%20much%20as%20in%20obscure%20turns%20of%20phrase%20in%20obsolete%20languages%2C%20in%20craft%20found%20in%20traditions%20of%20weaving%2C%20primitive%20manufacture%2C%20tribal%20cultures%20and%20those%20of%20the%20modern%20working%20class.%20It%20was%20the%20cinema%20that%2C%20above%20all%2C%20could%20take%20absorb%2C%20take%20on%2C%20such%20a%20span.%20Sound%2C%20picture%2C%20the%20minute%20gradations%20of%20colour%2C%20the%20moves%20of%20the%20camera%20%E2%80%93%20and%20above%20all%2C%20the%20cinema%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20capture%20silences%20that%20were%20not%20the%20%3Cem%3Eabsence%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20sound%2C%20but%20an%20audio-visual%20%3Cem%3Epresence%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20was%20unique%20to%20fully%20processed%20celluloid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShahani%20was%20of%20course%20saying%20this%20in%20a%20country%20with%20chronic%20cinematic%20overproduction%3A%20a%20%E2%80%98medium%E2%80%99%20(a%20term%20he%20disliked%2C%20as%20he%20did%20the%20concept%20of%20communication%20theory%20that%20converted%20all%20audiences%20into%20recipients%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98message%E2%80%99)%20being%20sought%20to%20be%20owned%20as%20much%20by%20the%20state%20as%20by%20the%20market.%20He%20redefined%20cinema%20in%20this%20sense%20of%20cinema.%20Widely%20seen%20as%20having%20been%20%E2%80%98sidelined%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20unable%20to%20make%20films%2C%20in%20a%20space%20that%20had%20powerful%20antagonists%20with%20significant%20political%20and%20economic%20interests.%20In%20a%20way%20he%20was%20marginal%20to%20those%20interests.%20In%20another%20way%2C%20he%20remained%20central%20to%20the%20entire%20discourse%2C%20a%20constant%20point%20of%20reference%20for%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20question%20of%20cinema%2C%20and%20the%20span%20of%20what%20the%20cinematic%20could%20straddle%20in%20a%20place%20like%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%20this%20related%20as%20much%20to%20unmade%20films%20as%20it%20did%20to%20completed%20ones.%20He%20could%20not%20make%20a%20full%20length%20film%20for%20over%20a%20decade%20after%20%3Cem%3EMaya%20Darpan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20then%20he%20did%20complete%20%3Cem%3ETarang%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20first%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20end%2C%20the%20only%2C%20fully%20realised%20instance%20of%20several%20truly%20epic%20works%20that%20he%20had%20planned%20and%2C%20sometimes%2C%20even%20scripted.%20Among%20the%20several%20that%20were%20in%20some%20stage%20of%20initial%20production%2C%20was%20a%20film%20on%20%3Cem%3EAnna%20Karenina%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20which%20he%20had%20provisionally%20cast%20Dimple%20Kapadia%2C%20another%20one%20on%20the%20history%20of%20cotton%20in%20the%20modern%20world%20which%2C%20if%20he%20had%20made%20it%2C%20would%20have%20been%20shot%20over%20three%20continents%20and%20spanned%20five%20hundred%20years%20of%20modern%20history.%20Less%20realised%2C%20but%20in%20some%20way%20into%20production%20was%20%3Cem%3EHamlet%3C%2Fem%3E%20featuring%20Michael%20Jackson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154125%2FDSC_4233-SS-03.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154125%2FDSC_4233-SS-03.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154125%2FDSC_4233-SS-03-300x146.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154125%2FDSC_4233-SS-03-1024x498.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698926%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESmita%20Patil%20ae%20Janaki%2C%20the%20working%20class%20protagonist%20of%20Tarang%20(1984).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20%3Cem%3ETarang%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20made%20two%20works%20of%20fiction%2C%20%3Cem%3EKasba%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EChar%20Adhyay%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adapting%20Chekhov%20and%20Tagore%20respectively.%20Both%20his%20completed%20works%20and%20several%20that%20remained%20incomplete%20or%20unrealised%2C%20were%20epic%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20both%20scale%20and%20structures%20of%20signification.%20He%20meant%20epic%20not%20exactly%20in%20Brecht%E2%80%99s%20sense%2C%20or%20even%20in%20Eisenstein%E2%80%99s%2C%20but%20rather%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20Kosambi%2C%20sometimes%20borrowing%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3EMahabharata%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20saw%20such%20epic%20structures%20as%20much%20in%20classical%20formations%20as%20buried%20under%20the%20dominance%20of%20the%20dramatic-lyrical%2C%20the%20form%20preferred%2C%20he%20said%2C%20by%20the%20modern%20bourgeoisie%3A%20forms%20such%20as%20the%20folk%2C%20or%20even%20of%20the%20proletariat%2C%20such%20as%20(we%20saw%20in%20%3Cem%3ETarang%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Elavani%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201990s%2C%20the%20form%20changed%3A%20the%20budgets%20he%20needed%20were%20not%20forthcoming%2C%20and%20an%20increasing%20abstraction%20%E2%80%93%20the%20way%20round%20the%20barriers%20of%20capital%E2%80%99s%20domination%20of%20value%20%E2%80%93%20appeared%20to%20him%20to%20be%20the%20only%20way%20forward.%20It%20was%20an%20abstraction%20that%20could%20be%20performed%20only%20by%20dancers%2C%20as%20against%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20Pandit%20Birju%20Maharaj%20in%20%3Cem%3EKhayal%20Gatha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Kelucharan%20Mahapatra%20in%20%3Cem%3EBhavantarana%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Alarmel%20Valli%2C%20among%20others%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EBamboo%20Flute%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20unrealised%20films%20included%20one%20with%20Pina%20Bausch.%20All%20of%20these%20are%20abstract%20in%20a%20somewhat%20particular%20sense%3A%20focusing%20on%20narrative%20sequence%2C%20usually%20driven%20by%20music%20%E2%80%93%20sequence%20being%20literally%20as%20important%20a%20concept%20for%20him%20as%20montage%20had%20been%20to%20one%20of%20his%20mentors%2C%20Sergei%20Eisenstein%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20performative%20mode%20that%20could%20sustain%20such%20sequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154935%2FDSC_4957-SS-03.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154935%2FDSC_4957-SS-03.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154935%2FDSC_4957-SS-03-300x187.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154935%2FDSC_4957-SS-03-1024x638.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698933%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22748%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EStone%20carver%20from%20Bhavantarana%20(1991).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it%20was%20not%20about%20what%20he%20was%20able%20to%20achieve%20in%20the%20cinema%20that%20defined%20him.%20In%20the%20myriad%20locations%20where%20he%20taught%2C%20showed%20his%20work%2C%20spoke%2C%20workshopped%2C%20at%20FTII%20and%20SRFTI%20and%20in%20several%20different%20spaces%20both%20formal%20and%20informal%2C%20it%20was%20an%20idea%20of%20what%20could%20be%20done%20%E2%80%93%20a%20condition%20of%20possibility%2C%20to%20quote%20him%20%E2%80%93%20that%20remains.%20And%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20cinema%20seems%20to%20have%20something%20to%20say%20to%20that%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshish%20Rajadhyaksha%20is%20a%20film%20historian%2C%20cultural%20theorist%20and%20occasional%20art%20curator.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708945240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26160329%2FKS.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkumar-shahani-redefined-the-cinema-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kumar%20Shahani%20was%20said%20to%20have%20been%20uncompromising.%20That%2C%20if%20any%2C%20was%20the%20word%20that%20famously%20defined%20him.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A186%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkumar-shahani-redefined-the-cinema-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Agnipath%20Scheme%20%E2%80%98Anyay%E2%80%99%20to%20Lakhs%20of%20Youth%2C%20Says%20Kharge%20in%20Letter%20to%20President%20Murmu%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154359%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-26-at-3.43.38-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20an%20attempt%20to%20draw%20the%20attention%20of%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20towards%20the%20Agnipath%20scheme%2C%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20has%20written%20a%20letter%20on%20Monday%2C%20February%2026%2C%20suggesting%20that%20the%20scheme%20has%20done%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Canyay%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(injustice)%20to%20lakhs%20of%20Indian%20youth%20seeking%20employment%20in%20the%20armed%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20letter%2C%20Kharge%20said%20that%20nearly%20two%20lakh%20young%20men%20and%20women%20were%20accepted%20into%20the%20three%20armed%20services%20%E2%80%93%20Navy%2C%20Army%20and%20Air%20Force%20%E2%80%93%20between%202019%20and%202022%20but%20were%20%E2%80%9Ccruelly%20denied%20the%20opportunity%20to%20serve%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20young%20men%20and%20women%20had%20struggled%20against%20all%20odds%20to%20pass%20gruelling%20mental%20and%20physical%20tests%20and%20a%20written%20exam.%20Until%20May%2031%2C%202022%20they%20believed%20that%20they%20had%20fulfilled%20their%20dreams%20and%20were%20waiting%20only%20for%20their%20joining%20letters.%20On%20that%20day%2C%20their%20dreams%20were%20shattered%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20end%20this%20recruitment%20process%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20the%20Agnipath%20scheme%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EMy%20letter%20to%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20President%20of%20India%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Frashtrapatibhvn%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40rashtrapatibhvn%3C%2Fa%3E)%20highlighting%20the%20gross%20injustice%20to%20almost%20two%20lakh%20young%20men%20and%20women%20whose%20future%20has%20become%20uncertain%20due%20to%20ending%20of%20regular%20recruitment%20process%20and%20imposing%20Agnipath%20Scheme%20for%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20by%20the%20Union%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FnZceaXpKs0%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FnZceaXpKs0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20(%40kharge)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkharge%2Fstatus%2F1761990787313934415%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2026%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharge%20also%20referred%20to%20former%20chief%20of%20Army%20staff%20General%20M.M.%20Naravane%E2%80%99s%20yet%20to%20be%20published%20memoir%2C%20in%20which%20he%20had%20written%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctaken%20by%20surprise%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20earlier%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fex-army-chief-gen-naravanes-memoirs-delayed-amazon-cancels-january-orders-not-before-may%5C%22%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20memoir%20titled%3Cem%3E%20Four%20Stars%20of%20Destiny%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20earlier%20to%20be%20released%20on%20January%2015%20(which%20is%20Army%20Day)%20is%20%E2%80%9Cawaiting%20clearance%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20Union%20ministry%20of%20defence%20and%20the%20Union%20ministry%20of%20external%20affairs%20and%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20released%20before%20the%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharge%20said%20that%20the%20scheme%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdiscriminatory%E2%80%9D%20and%20creates%20%E2%80%9Cparallel%20cadres%20of%20soldiers%20who%20are%20expected%20to%20work%20on%20similar%20tasks%2C%20but%20with%20very%20similar%20emoluments%2C%20benefits%20and%20prospects.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20majority%20of%20the%20Agniveers%20will%20be%20released%20into%20an%20uncertain%20job%20market%20after%20four%20years%20of%20service%2C%20which%20some%20have%20argued%20could%20affect%20social%20stability%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20president%20underlined%20that%20his%20main%20purpose%20of%20writing%20the%20letter%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Chighlight%20the%3Cem%3E%20anyay%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20injustice%20inflicted%20on%20the%20lakhs%20of%20youth%20whose%20dreams%20did%20not%20materialise%20despite%20the%20solemn%20promise%20made%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNot%20only%20did%20they%20spend%20years%20in%20pursuit%20of%20this%20dream%20but%20each%20of%20the%2050%20lakh%20applicants%20had%20to%20pay%20Rs%20250%20to%20collect%20the%20application%20forms%20and%20the%20amount%20was%20never%20refunded%2C%20which%20amounts%20to%20a%20hefty%20Rs%20125%20crore%20taken%20from%20these%20youngsters.%20The%20resulting%20frustration%20has%20even%20led%20to%20several%20reported%20deaths%20by%20suicide%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kharge%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversial%20Agnipath%20scheme%20revamped%20military%20recruitment%20to%20a%20four-year%20tour%20of%20duty%20for%2075%25%20of%20recruits.%20The%20remaining%2025%25%20would%20be%20absorbed%20on%20a%20permanent%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fagnipath-scheme-death-knell-indian-democracy-hindu-rashtra%5C%22%3EThe%C2%A0Agnipath%20Scheme%20May%20Be%20Designed%20to%20Ring%20the%20Death%20Knell%20of%20Indian%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-nodal-agency-resettlement-released-agniveers%5C%22%3EParliamentary%20Committee%20on%20Defence%20%E2%80%9Crecommended%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20setting%20up%20a%20separate%20nodal%20agency%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20that%20will%20help%20Agniveers%20who%20are%20not%20retained%20by%20the%20military%20in%20accessing%20educational%20and%20resettlement%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUrging%20Murmu%E2%80%99s%20intervention%2C%20Kharge%20appealed%20to%20her%20to%20ensure%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Enyay%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20justice%20is%20done.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Monday%2C%20former%20Rajasthan%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Sachin%20Pilot%20reiterated%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20stand%20that%20the%20selected%20youth%20should%20be%20given%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20can%20spend%20crores%20of%20rupees%20on%20events%20like%20G20%2C%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20aeroplane%2C%20projects%20like%20Central%20Vista%20and%20their%20publicity.%20But%20playing%20with%20the%20recruitment%20process%20of%20the%20Army%20just%20to%20save%20money%20can%20become%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20security%20of%20the%20country.%20Our%20request%20is%20that%20the%20youth%20who%20were%20selected%20should%20be%20given%20jobs%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pilot%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708944315000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26154359%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-26-at-3.43.38-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fagnipath-scheme-anyay-to-lakhs-of-youth-says-kharge-in-letter-to-president-murmu%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20letter%2C%20Kharge%20said%20that%20about%20two%20lakh%20youth%20were%20selected%20but%20not%20given%20jobs%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98discriminatory%E2%80%99%20scheme.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fagnipath-scheme-anyay-to-lakhs-of-youth-says-kharge-in-letter-to-president-murmu%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israeli%20military%20presents%20a%20plan%20for%20a%20Rafah%20offensive%20to%20the%20War%20Cabinet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708943037000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22